cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SD, cs.MM, cs.HC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper deals with online social networks and their retention of users. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also likely as the paper discusses the economic and psychological implications of user retention on social networks. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper proposes an analytical model to determine the value of an access to the social network. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible category as the paper mentions the rate at which sources generate content on social networks. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the attention budget of users on social networks.
